Colours in Schell Scripting
----------------------------
-> Colour Syntax : \e[<code>m]
-> \e mean escaping the special chars
-> Red="\e[31m"
-> Green="\e[32m"
-> Yellow="\e[33m"
-> Normal="\e[0m"

---------------------------
-> To enable colours : echo -e 
-> To end the colour : ex- \e[32m Hello colour \e[0m
